entries.title: UN chief urges nations to consider deploying forces to help Haiti
entries.description: United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres has urged the international community to consider deploying forces to Haiti to address growing humanitarian and security crises in the country.

entries.title: How not to run out of money in retirement
entries.description: No one wants to run out of money before they die.

entries.title: Floods submerge homes in Nigeria. At least 80 dead
entries.description: Seventy-six people have died as their boat capsized while they tried to flee dangerously high floodwaters that have inundated swathes of southern Nigeria.

entries.title: ISIS-linked militants are threatening huge natural gas reserves the world needs badly right now
entries.description: Asmani Dadi had heard rumors about the insurgents. Then, one day, they came true.

entries.title: 'No room for compromise' on Taiwan's sovereignty, President Tsai says in National Day speech
entries.description: Taiwan's President Tsai Ing-wen said Monday there is "no room for compromise" over the self-ruled island's sovereignty but she is willing to work with China to find "mutually acceptable ways" to maintain peace across the Taiwan Strait.

entries.title: Funeral rites begin for victims of mass shooting and stabbing at Thailand nursery
entries.description: Buddhist funeral rites have begun in the grieving town of Uthai Sawan in northern Thailand, where families are mourning the loss of children killed in a massacre at a day care center.

entries.title: North Korea says missile tests are practice for 'tactical nuclear strikes' on South Korea
entries.description: North Korean state media has broken its silence over the country's recent spate of missile tests, claiming they were part of a series of simulated procedures intended to demonstrate its readiness to fire tactical nuclear warheads at potential targets in South Korea.
